H1.text: Cleeve Hill is the highest point in which range of English hills. Chiltern Hills

H2.text: Cleeve Hill is the highest point in which range of English hills. Pennines

H3.text: Cleeve Hill is the highest point in which range of English hills. Cotswold

A4.text: The highest point is Cleeve Hill at 1,083 ft (330 m), just east of Cheltenham.

A5.text: This feature, known as the Cotswold escarpment or the Cotswold Edge, is a result of the uplifting (tilting) of the limestone layer, exposing its broken edge.
